-- Taiwan Stocks: Chimei Innolux, Deltamac, Far Eastone Telecom
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-06-26T05:48:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-26/taiwan-stocks-chimei-innolux-deltamac-far-eastone-telecom.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 0.4 percent to 7,137.93, the fourth
day of declines and the longest losing streak since March 20.
The gauge has climbed 0.9 percent this year, its first six-month
gain since the second half of 2010.  Chimei Innolux Corp. (3481)  (3481 TT) retreated 2.8 percent to
NT$12.10, the biggest drop since June 4. The island’s biggest
flat panel maker approved a plan to sell 600 million new shares,
according to a statement to the  Taiwan Stock Exchange .  Deltamac Taiwan Co. (6144)  (6144 TT) surged 6.9 percent to
NT$10.90, the biggest advance since May 25. Japan’s Culture
Convenience Club Co. plans to pay NT$244 million for a 33.4
percent stake in the film distributor in a private placement,
Deltamac said in a statement to the stock exchange.  Far Eastone Telecommunications Co. (4904)  (4904 TT) gained 1.4
percent to NT$65.40. The phone operator was raised to neutral
from underweight at HSBC Holdings Plc.  MStar Semiconductor Inc. (3697)  (3697 TT) surged for a second day,
gaining 6.2 percent to NT$207, the highest since May 18.
 Mediatek Inc. (2454)  (2454 TT) agreed to buy the chip designer in a
deal worth $3.8 billion, both companies said in a statement on
June 22. Mediatek retreated 2.1 percent to NT$274.50.  To contact the reporter on this story:
